__________('battery',)__________


Positive Reviews:

---'good battery performance, it last the hole day with all services running.' **** 'good'
---"it's not big issue at all, bur it would be great if htc could include the earphones with microphone.the battery duration might be an issue, so i recommend to buy:- anker external battery pack- hyperion at&t; htc vivid 4g 2 x battery + chargerfor less than $400 usd this is an excellent choice for an android phone." **** 'less'

Negative Reviews:

---'fortunately my wife had not sent back the first htc vivid that we received so i was able to pull the battery out of that phone.the battery from the first phone fired up the second phone and the phone was able to connect to the at&t; network, unlike the first phone.' **** 'able'
---'battery however was completely dead and took 12 hours to charge to 75 percent.' **** 'dead'
---'i chose this over the htc sensation because of the replaceable battery even though the talk and standby times are significantly less.' **** 'replaceable'
---"the phone works great, its incredible fast and it is the last phone with the freedom you need to add extra memory since the new htc models doesn't have the micro sd slot and not removable battery (or back cover).this phone comes already unlocked from the provider and you don't have to introduce an unlocking code." **** 'removable'


